---
// DAY-172 / DAY-173. Server-rendered placeholder for the
// `<Hero client:only>` island.
//
// The hero is a React island with `client:only="react"` because
// framer-motion's scroll hooks (`useScroll`, `MotionValue`) ship
// browser-only code that breaks Astro's static build. `client:only`
// renders nothing on the server by default, which up to DAY-171
// meant the static HTML looked like this on first paint:
//
//     (empty astro-island)
//     <section id="how-it-works">Three steps. No meetings…</section>
//     …
//
// So browsers painted the "How it works" section at the top of the
// viewport, then — a few hundred ms later, when the React bundle
// finished loading — `HeroAnimated` mounted with a `h-[300vh]`
// scroll zone above HowItWorks and shoved everything downward.
// Scroll position stayed at 0, so from the user's perspective the
// page snapped back to the top and the hero appeared where
// HowItWorks had just been. Classic CLS glitch.
//
// DAY-172 added this file as the `slot="fallback"` for the hero
// island, mirroring HeroAnimated's outer structure
// (`relative h-[300vh]` outer, `sticky top-0 h-screen` inner) so
// the scroll zone is reserved server-side with the exact
// dimensions the hydrated animated hero will use. That fixed the
// 300vh jump.
//
// DAY-173 closed the remaining residual flicker: the fallback
// originally carried HeroStatic's copy ("The report of your day,
// written from evidence" + long pitch paragraph), which only
// reduced-motion users ever see once the React island hydrates.
// For the 99%+ of visitors whose JS is enabled and motion is not
// reduced, the React island hydrates to `HeroAnimated`, which
// paints `IntroHero` at scroll = 0 — copy is "Dayseam" + "Automatic
// daily reports, pulled from every tool you already ship in" +
// "Scroll to see how". So even though the container height didn't
// shift on hydration, the visible TEXT content flipped from the
// HeroStatic-flavoured h1 to the IntroHero one, which read as a
// glitch on first load.
//
// This file now mirrors IntroHero's copy exactly so hydration is
// visually silent: same h1 ("Dayseam"), same pitch line, same
// scroll affordance, same sticky-centred layout inside the same
// 300vh container. The React hero replaces the DOM subtree on
// hydration but the *rendered result* is pixel-close, so the
// hand-off is imperceptible.
//
// Reduced-motion users (served `HeroStatic` after hydration) still
// see a content change — from this fallback's "Dayseam" pitch into
// HeroStatic's three-step layout — but reduced-motion paths
// opt out of motion anyway, and the replacement happens once at
// scroll 0 in the same visual band, which reads as "the static
// variant loaded" rather than mid-read page shift.
//
// SEO / no-JS footnote: search crawlers and JS-disabled visitors
// that don't execute the React island see this fallback as the
// page content. The h1 is "Dayseam" (brand term) and the pitch
// line carries the product positioning; the richer product copy
// lives downstream in HowItWorks, ConnectorGrid, TrustStrip, and
// DownloadCTA, which all render as static Astro components and
// remain reachable without JS. The standalone `<noscript>` block
// that lived in index.astro pre-DAY-172 is therefore still
// retired — this fallback does the same job.
---

<section
  class="relative h-[300vh]"
  aria-label="How Dayseam works, loading an animated walkthrough"
>
  <div
    class="sticky top-0 flex h-screen flex-col items-center justify-center overflow-hidden px-6 text-center"
  >
    <div
      aria-hidden="true"
      class="absolute inset-0"
      style="background: radial-gradient(circle at 50% 45%, #1f1f24 0%, #14141a 45%, #0a0a0e 100%);"
    >
    </div>

    <h1
      class="relative z-10 text-balance text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-50 sm:text-7xl"
    >
      Dayseam
    </h1>
    <p
      class="relative z-10 mt-4 max-w-xl text-balance text-base text-zinc-300 sm:mt-5 sm:text-lg"
    >
      Automatic daily reports, pulled from every tool you already ship in
    </p>
    <p
      class="relative z-10 mt-6 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-zinc-500 sm:mt-8"
      aria-hidden="true"
    >
      Scroll to see how
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
